<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<span id="head-6ad57b7eb9cde338fb3b20b1cfb152c7e967f989"><h2 id="l2">Enforcement of Policies</h2></span>
<p id="l4">
You are a PrintWiki editor. Since PrintWiki has no editor-in-chief or top-down article approval mechanism, active participants make copyedits and corrections to the format and content problems they see. So the participants are both writers and editors. Individual users thus enforce most policies and guidelines by editing pages, and discussing matters with each other. 
</p>
<p id="l6">
Some policies, such as <a title="PrintWiki/Policies/Vandalism" href="Vandalism">Vandalism</a>, are enforced by Administrators by blocking users. Some features of the software which could potentially be misused, such as deleting pages and locking pages from editing, are restricted to Administrators, who are experienced and trusted members of the community. 
</p>
